# PluvianAI — Cursor rules (living document)

## Project path (critical)

- **Always use the main project root:** `C:\Users\user\Desktop\AgentGuard`
- All file reads, writes, and edits must target this path. **Do not use worktree paths** (e.g. paths under `.cursor\worktrees\AgentGuard\...` or `C:\Users\user\.cursor\worktrees\...`).
- If the workspace or tool reports a different “workspace path,” still read and write files under `C:\Users\user\Desktop\AgentGuard` so that changes land in the repo you care about.
- When in doubt, prefer the Desktop path above over any other workspace root.

## Language

- **Use English only** in code, comments, commit messages, and in-app user-facing copy (UI strings, tooltips, docs). Do not add or leave Korean (or other non-English) in the codebase unless the product explicitly targets that locale.

## Living document

- When you fix a non-obvious bug, learn a new pattern in this codebase, or get corrected on a recurring mistake, **add that to this file (or the relevant section)** right away.
- Keep this document up to date so future sessions and other readers benefit. Treat it as a **living document**, not a one-time setup.
